properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 30 at 2:29PM PST until January 31 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northeast winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Los Angeles and Ventura County mountains and valleys
except for the San Gabriel Valley.

* WHEN...From 10 PM this evening to noon PST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The strongest winds will be in the Los
Angeles County mountains in and around the Highway 14 corridor,
the Santa Monica mountains, and in the hills surrounding the
eastern Ventura County valleys.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO NOON PST FRIDAY
